        <h2>About Us</h2><hr>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-12">
             <p><b>Yuva Kalyan Parishad (YKP)</b> is a thought which has the capacity of building a new, developed and complete nation. We strive to expand our outreach to all those who are in need. Unfortunately our state Bihar lacks in self sufficiency. Engulfed with problems like unemployment, unawareness, poverty and poor education which restricts its grouping in developing state category. Even though our state is heading towards development, the problem slows down the process of development.</p>
             <p>Within the boundaries of the state every section of society, community, cast, and religion live. It is unfortunate that most of the youth in our state lacks commitment while the responsibility lies on their shoulders. The main reason behind making our country immovable and under developed is lack of awareness and gainful employment.</p>
            <p><b>Yuva Kalyan Parishad</b> was formed in the year 2012 in state capital of Bihar (Patna) for eradicating the darkness within the society which is due of unawareness, poverty, unemployment and to make youth educated and Self dependent.</p>
            <h3>Aim of Yuva Kalyan Parishad</h3><hr>
            <p>Our main aim is to make the youth educated, self dependent, employed, competent and responsible person through education, livelihood and training. As well as to make the availability of the participation of youth, writing the future of our country on the map of world.</p>
            <p>We believe that every person has the right to have a life having basic amenities, access to resources and to develop with dignity. In order to make it a reality we need to strengthen the social structure of the society. So we aim at:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Social development and Upliftment for those live in poverty and distress through assistance and guidance.</li>
              <li>To assist in the process of social integration and personal realization of underprivileged children, young people, adults and families. Students from OBC, SC and ST communities are enrolled in professional courses free of cost.</li>
              <li>To encourage and popularize voluntary work.</li>
              <li>To fight against exploitation, injustice and corruption if found against any individual, class, community in the society.</li>
              <li>To provide help under health & nutrition services for women and children.</li>
              <li>To endorse the human rights and in particular the rights of the children and young people as well as the rights of underprivileged groups and communities.</li>
              <li>To provide a forum for the exchange of ideas on the social, cultural and educational conditions of society.</li>
            </ol>
              <h3>Program Running by Yuva Kalyan Parishad</h3><hr>
              <p><b>Jan Siksha Abhiyan</b></p>
              <p><b>Skill Development Training Program</b></p>
              <p><b>Self Help Group</b></p>
              <p><b>Free Employment Exchange Programme</b></p>
              <p><b>Expansion of E-Governance through RTI</b></p>
              <p><b>Social Change For Social Impact</b></p>
              <h3>Working experience of YKP</h3><hr>
              <p><b>Year, 2012</b></p>
              <p>Yuva Kalyan Parishad was established with the aim of commitment to the welfare of people from the most under privileged strata of society without distinction of caste & creed. Its emphasis will be to focus on the overall development of society through empowerment of people.</p>
              <p><b>Year, 2013</b></p>
              <p>Yuva Kalyan Parishad in its second year aimed at fulfilling the basic necessities of people and introduced several programs such as:-</p>
              <ul>
                <li><b>Jan Siksha Abhiyan –</b> There is a lack of education in our country, especially among backward classes, scheduled castes and tribes. Yuva Kalyan Parishad undertook a project to address this problem, known as Most Matric Scholarship. In which we linked students from SC / ST community in Bihar to Scholarship Scheme for engineering courses, the organization selected and enrolled students to various Engineering colleges across India.</li>
                <li><b>CROWD FUNDING -</b> Development of villages, addressing their needs and to overcome the problems was done through small crowd funding. The project was launched at Paliganj block of Patna district was expanded around the various districts respectively;<b> Block of Samastipur Samastipur, Rohtas Dinara Block, Block Muzaffarpur and Motihari, </b>crowd funding project in year 2013 led to digging of wells in several villages. Under these several roofs in schools were built and facility for safe drinking water was provided.</li>
              </ul>
              <p><b>Year, 2014</b></p>
              <p>In 2014, the Yuva kalyan Parishad ran Jan Siksha Abhiyans, to other areas such as government departments, Bihar commission for Schedule Castes & Schedule Tribes. Students from various communities were enrolled in professional colleges across the country with better opportunities of growth provided.</p>
              <p>Development training provided through <b>SELF HELP GROUP</b> in the entire state. Yuva Kalyan Parishad’s Objective to create associate partner became reality as in the 8 districts of 18 districts all over the place we started self-help groups empowering women and propagation of e- governance was also done making people more aware.</p>
              <p><b>Year,2015</b></p>
              <p>Government recognized our organization since formation Yuva Kalyan Parishad educated masses according to their interest and programmes like NDLM training run by the government several skill development programmes were run creating awareness among the information was spread across every section of the community. During this period around 3 thousand unemployed registered at registry offices and around 700 were given employment within 2 months through Yuva Kalyan Parishad’s network and personal contacts.</p>
              <h3>Strength of Yuva Kalyan Parishad</h3><hr>
              <p>Strength of an organization depends upon the strategy that implies to execute the programme & policies. We have 150 Associate Partners and 30 Block Co-Ordinators in 35 Districts of Bihar.</p>
              <p>More than 200 Skill training centers are running in all over Bihar providing different skill training to people according to their interest & requirement.</p>
              <p>For its remarkable achievement in counseling providing admission of student in different technical & professional courses in various colleges in India Yuva Kalyan Parishad has authorized to work as a Nodal Agency for this project.</p>
